    "summary": "I am a researcher and educator with a PhD in Economic Sociology, specialized in business networks, business resilience and diversity & inclusion in entrepreneurship. I have been involved in research-related and policy-making activities for the past 15 years while working for higher education institutes, NGO's, private consultancy and governmental institutions.\n\nBusiness networks and diversity are changing our entrepreneurial ecosystems, that is why my research line of diversity in entrepreneurship focuses on the business networks and the conditions for women, minority groups and migrants to enter the market, bring novel products and create inclusive business communities. \n\nFor every start there is an end, that is why my parallel research line (Fenix Project) has collected more than a thousand entrepreneurial stories from entrepreneurs who have had failures and bankruptcy. Together with students and colleagues, we analyze the resiliency strategies and adaptability in those hard times. Those lessons are being shared to enrich public policy, and entrepreneurship education.",
